{# Renders form-LEVEL (root) validation errors — those that attach to the form
   itself rather than a specific field. The main real-world source is an
   oversized multipart upload (POST body over PHP post_max_size), which Symfony
   reports as a root error; a constraint on a data property with no rendered
   field can also bubble here. The per-field {{ form_errors(form.x) }} calls and
   form_end()'s form_rest never render root errors, so without this the form
   returns a silent HTTP 422 with nothing shown to the user.

   Usage: {% include 'components/_form_root_errors.html.twig' with { form: myForm } %}
   immediately after {{ form_start(...) }}. #}
{% if form.vars.errors|length > 0 %}
    <div class="alert alert-error mb-4">{{ form_errors(form) }}</div>
{% endif %}
